children.name: hwAcl
children.description: The HUAWEI-ACL-MIB contains objects to configure ACL module, including ACL group, rule and acl accelerate, and query the current ACL configuration and status. This MIB module objects indicate hwAclNumGroupTable, hwAclBasicRuleTable, hwAclAdvanceRuleTable, hwAclIfRuleTable, hwAclEthernetFrameRuleTable, hwAclIpv6BasicRuleTable, hwAclIpv6AdvanceRuleTable, hwAclIpv6IfRuleTable, hwAclCompileEnableFlag, hwAclCompileNumGroupTable, hwAclIpv6NumGroupTable and acl trap. To filter data packets, a series of rules need to be configured on the device. These rules are defined by ACL (Access Control List), which are a series of sequential rules consisting of rule permit or deny statements. The rules are described by source address, destination address and port number of data packets. ACL classifies data packets through these device interface applied rules, by which the device decides which packets can be received and which should be rejected.

children.name: hwAclNumGroupTable
children.description: The table of ACL group information including match order, step, description and so on

children.name: hwAclNumGroupEntry
children.description: An entry containing characters of an acl group

children.name: hwAclNumGroupAclNum
children.description: The index of acl group, identifying an ACL. The object specifies the range of an ACL number. The basic ACL is represented by the number in the range 2000 through 2999. The advanced ACL is represented by the number in the range 3000 through 3999. The interface-based ACL is represented by the number in the range 1000 to 1999. The User Defined ACL is represented by the number in the range 5000 through 5999. The User ACL is represented by the number in the range 6000 through 9999. The Mpls ACL is represented by the number in the range 10000 through 10999. The name ACL is represented by the number in the range 42768 through 76535.

children.name: hwAclNumGroupMatchOrder
children.description: The object indicates the match order of rules. 'config' means matching ACL rules in the configuration sequence, 'auto' means the ACL rules are matched following the 'Depth-first' principle. Enumeration: 'auto': 2, 'config': 1.

children.name: hwAclNumGroupSubitemNum
children.description: The total number of the rules in the acl group.

children.name: hwAclNumGroupStep
children.description: The object indicates the step value of number acl. Step here refers to the difference between each ID. For instance, given the step is set to 5, the IDs are the multiples of 5 beginning with 5. The ACL IDs change along with the step. When the step is 5, the ACL IDs are 5, 10, and 15 and so on. However, when the step is set to 2, the IDs turn to 2, 4, and 6 and so on.

children.name: hwAclNumGroupDescription
children.description: The object indicates the description of this acl group. The object describes the usage of an ACL with a word or a sentence.

children.name: hwAclNumGroupCountClear
children.description: Reset the statistics of ACL group. Enumeration: 'cleared': 1, 'notUsed': 2.

children.name: hwAclNumGroupRowStatus
children.description: RowStatus, Now support three value:CreateAndGo,Active,Destroy.

children.name: hwAclNumGroupAclName
children.description: The object indicates the name of an acl group, The first character must be start with a to z or A to Z, and the length cannot exceed 64 character.

children.name: hwAclNumGroupAclType
children.description: The type of ACL group. Enumeration: 'mpls': 6, 'mac': 7, 'link': 3, 'user': 4, 'basic': 1, 'interface': 5, 'ucl': 8, 'advanced': 2.

children.name: hwAclBasicRuleTable
children.description: Configure the rule for basic acl group.

children.name: hwAclBasicRuleEntry
children.description: Each entry is a rule of basic acl.

children.name: hwAclBasicAclNum
children.description: The index of basic acl group, the index range is (1..99 | 2000..2999 | 42768..76535 ).

children.name: hwAclBasicSubitem
children.description: The objects specifies the number of an ACL rule. If the number specified has been assigned to an ACL rule, the new rule will overwrite the old one, which is equal to editing the old rule. If the number is not assigned, the system will define a rule with the number and insert it to the place corresponding to its number. If no number is specified, the system will define a rule, assign a number to it and add it into the ACL. It will be placed at the end of the ACL when configuration sequence is adopted; otherwise, it will be placed based on the 'Depth-first' principle. When ACL rules are following the 'Depth-first' principle, the number of an ACL rule must be given 0 ,but it will be assigned by step automatically;otherwise,this rule will not be created.

children.name: hwAclBasicAct
children.description: The object indicates the action of a basic acl rule. 'deny' means discarding the packets that meet the condition, 'permit' means permitting the packets that meet the condition. Enumeration: 'deny': 2, 'permit': 1.

children.name: hwAclBasicSrcIp
children.description: The object indicates the source IP-address of a basic acl rule.

children.name: hwAclBasicSrcWild
children.description: The object indicates the source IP-address wild of a basic acl rule.

children.name: hwAclBasicTimeRangeIndex
children.description: The object indicates the time range of a basic acl rule. When the current time is in time range, the rule is valid. Zero value declares that the acl rule has no time range. The invalid value is 0.

children.name: hwAclBasicFragments
children.description: The object indicates the type of the packet. 0: fragmentSubseq, indicating that the packet is a subsequent fragment 1: fragment, indicating that the packet is a fragment 2: nonFragment, indicating that the packet is not a fragment 3: nonSubseq, indicating that the packet is not a subsequent fragment 4: fragmentSpeFirst, indicating that the packet is the first fragment 255: none, invalid value This object cannot be modified once a rule is created. Enumeration: 'none': 255, 'fragment': 1, 'nonFragment': 2, 'fragmentSubseq': 0, 'fragmentSpeFirst': 4, 'nonSubseq': 3.

children.name: hwAclBasicLog
children.description: The object indicates whether to log the matched packets. The log contents include sequence number of ACL rule, packets passed or discarded, upper layer protocol type over IP, source/destination address, source/destination port number, and number of packets.

children.name: hwAclBasicEnable
children.description: The object indicates whether the rule is valid or invalid.

children.name: hwAclBasicCount
children.description: The object indicates the statistics of matched packets by the rule.

children.name: hwAclBasicVrfName
children.description: The object indicates the VRF name of this rule. It specifies the VPN-instance to which the packet belongs.

children.name: hwAclBasicRowStatus
children.description: RowStatus, Now support three value:CreateAndGo,Active and Destroy.

children.name: hwAclBasicDescription
children.description: The object indicates the description of this basic rule. The object describes the usage of an ACL with a word or a sentence.

children.name: hwVlanMIBTable
children.description: Describes the VLAN basic attributes, used for managing a VLAN, including creating, modifying, querying, and deleting a VLAN, and configuring standard ports of a VLAN. The index of this table is hwVlanIndex.

children.name: hwVlanMIBEntry
children.description: Describes the VLAN basic attributes, used for managing a VLAN, including creating, modifying, querying, and deleting a VLAN, and configuring standard ports of a VLAN. The index of this entry is hwVlanIndex.

children.name: hwVlanIndex
children.description: Indicates the VLAN ID. Range: 1-4093. VLAN 1 is the native VLAN. It cannot be deleted, but its attributes can be modified.

children.name: hwVlanName
children.description: Indicates the VLAN tag. Identifying the VLAN is like naming the VLAN, which facilitates management. Range: a string of 0-32 characters Default: null character string

children.name: hwVlanPorts
children.description: Indicates the list of the standard ports in the VLAN. If the VLAN contains a port, the corresponding bit of the port is set to 1. The value of hwVlanPorts is an octet string. One bit in each octet indicates one port, so the octet string can indicate eight ports. When a bit is set to 0, it indicates that the corresponding port does not belong to this VLAN. When a bit is set to 1, it indicates that the corresponding port belongs to this VLAN. The order is as follows: The maximum number of ports in a slot is 64, so the ports need to occupy eight octets. The order, from left to right, is presented as eight groups, 0-7, 8-15, 16-23, 24-31, 32-39, 40-47, 48-55, and 56-63. In each octet, the port IDs in ascending order are presented from low bit to high bit. For example, ports 0/11/2 and 0/11/3 need to added to VLAN 2. The values of hwVlanPorts of the upstream ports (ports 0/11/2 and 0/11/3) to be added is calculated as follows: For ports 0-7 in slot 11, their corresponding character string positions are 76543210, and after ports 0/11/2 and 0/11/3 are added, the bitmap is 00001100 00000000 00000000 00000000, and the string is 0c 00 00 00 00 00 00 00. Assuming that the other slots do not have any port that is added to the VLAN, the character string of each of these slots is 0x0000000000000000. According to the ascending order of slot from left to right, the character strings of ports 0/11/2 and 0/11/3 are as follows: 0000000000000000 0000000000000000 0000000000000000 0000000000000000 0000000000000000 0000000000000000 0000000000000000 0000000000000000 0000000000000000 0000000000000000 0000000000000000 0c00000000000000 0000000000000000 0000000000000000 0000000000000000 0000000000000000

children.name: hwVlanType
children.description: Indicates the VLAN type. Options: 1. superVlan(1) -indicates super VLAN. 2. commonVlan(2) -indicates common VLAN. 3. subVlan(3) -indicates sub VLAN, the value is not supported. 4. primaryVlan(4) -indicates primary VLAN, the value is not supported. 5. secondaryVlan(5) -indicates secondary VLAN, the value is not supported. 6. regionVlan(6) -indicates region VLAN, the value is not supported. 7. smartVlan(7) -indicates smart VLAN. 8. muxVlan(8) -indicates MUX VLAN. 9. multiVlan(9) -indicates multi VLAN. VLAN 1 supports the modify operation on hwVlanType. For other VLANs, during the creation of a VLAN, hwVlanType must be specified.  Enumeration: 'commonVlan': 2, 'regionVlan': 6, 'subVlan': 3, 'muxVlan': 8, 'multiVlan': 9, 'secondaryVlan': 5, 'primaryVlan': 4, 'superVlan': 1, 'smartVlan': 7.

children.name: hwVlanMacFilter
children.description: The flag indicates whether to use mac filter. 1. true(1): use mac filter 2. false(2): not use mac filter

children.name: hwVlanMcastUnknownProtos
children.description: multicast unknown protocals flag in the VLAN field

children.name: hwExistInterface
children.description: The virtual interface used by VLAN

children.name: hwVlanInterfaceIndex
children.description: The index of the VLAN interface.

children.name: hwVlanMacLearn
children.description: The flag indicates whether to open mac learning.

children.name: hwVlanStatus
children.description: Status of VLAN. Options: 1. other(1) -The following enumerated values is not supported. 2. permanent(2) -The following enumerated values is not supported. 3. dynamicGvrp(3) -The following enumerated values is not supported.  Enumeration: 'permanent': 2, 'other': 1, 'dynamicGvrp': 3.

children.name: hwVlanCreationTime
children.description: The time of creating VLAN.

children.name: hwVlanPriority
children.description: Indicates the 802.1p priority of a VLAN. Range: 0-7, 255 The larger the value, the higher the priority. If the query operation is performed before hwVlanPriority is configured, the query result is 255, which is invalid. The meaning of each value is as follows: best-effort: Best-effort priority(0) background: Background priority(1) spare: Spare priority(2) excellent-effort: Excellent-effort priority(3) controlled-load: Controlled-load priority(4) video: Video priority(5) voice: Voice priority(6) network-management: Network-management priority(7)

children.name: hwVlanRowStatus
children.description: Indicates the row status, used for creating or deleting a VLAN. Options: 1. active(1) 2. createAndGo(4) 3. destroy(6) To create a VLAN, you must specify hwVlanType and set hwVlanRowStatus to createAndGo(4) to perform the set operation. Other attributes of the VLAN are optional. However, hwVlanPorts cannot be configured at the same time. To delete a VLAN, set hwVlanRowStatus to destroy(6) to perform the set operation. During query, the value of this leaf is the fixed active(1).

children.name: hwVlanAttrib
children.description: Indicates the VLAN attribute. The following enumerated values are supported: Options: 1. common(1) -indicates common VLAN. 2. qinq(2) -indicates QinQ VLAN. 3. stacking(3) -indicates stacking VLAN. 4. subVlan(4) -indicates sub VLAN. During the creation of a VLAN, if this leaf is not specified, common(1) is adopted by default. You can perform the set operation on this leaf to modify the VLAN attribute. The value of hwVlanAttrib must not be subvlan(4). The value can be subvlan(4) only in the read operation. Adding a VLAN to or deleting a VLAN from a super VLAN must be performed through hwVlanAggregationTable.  Enumeration: 'stacking': 3, 'subVlan': 4, 'common': 1, 'qinq': 2.

children.name: hwVlanSuperID
children.description: Indicates the ID of the super VLAN corresponding to the sub VLAN. Range: -1, 2-4093 This leaf is read-only. When the VLAN is not a sub VLAN, -1 is returned.

children.name: hwVlanForwarding
children.description: Indicates the VLAN forwarding policy. Options: 1. vlanMac(1) -indicates forwarding based on the VLAN+MAC. 2. vlanConnect(2) -indicates forwarding based on the SVLAN+CVLAN. During the creation of a VLAN, if this leaf is not specified, vlanMac(1) is adopted by default. You can perform the set operation on this leaf to modify the VLAN forwarding policy. The VLAN forwarding policy can also be configured in hwForwardingMode of hwVlanSrvProfTable. If a VLAN service profile is bound to the VLAN, the configuration in the VLAN service profile takes effect.  Enumeration: 'vlanConnect': 2, 'vlanMac': 1.

children.name: hwVlanPolicyBroadcast
children.description: Indicates the VLAN-based forwarding policy for the broadcast packets. Options: 1. forward(1) -indicates that the broadcast packets are transparently transmitted. 2. discard(2) -indicates that the broadcast packets are discarded. During the creation of a VLAN, if this leaf is not specified, forward(1) is adopted by default. You can perform the set operation on this leaf to modify the VLAN-based forwarding policy for the broadcast packets. The VLAN-based forwarding policy for the broadcast packets can also be configured in hwPolicyBroadcast of hwVlanSrvProfTable. If a VLAN service profile is bound to the VLAN, the configuration in the VLAN service profile takes effect.  Enumeration: 'forward': 1, 'discard': 2.

children.name: hwVlanPolicyMulticast
children.description: Indicates the VLAN-based forwarding policy for the unknown multicast packets. Options: 1. forward(1) -indicates that the unknown multicast packets are transparently transmitted. 2. discard(2) -indicates that the unknown multicast packets are discarded. During the creation of a VLAN, if this leaf is not specified, forward(1) is adopted by default. You can perform the set operation on this leaf to modify the VLAN-based forwarding policy for the unknown multicast packets. The VLAN-based forwarding policy for the unknown multicast packets can also be configured in hwPolicyMulticast of hwVlanSrvProfTable. If a VLAN service profile is bound to the VLAN, the configuration in the VLAN service profile takes effect.  Enumeration: 'forward': 1, 'discard': 2.

children.name: hwVlanPolicyUnknowncast
children.description: Indicates the VLAN-based forwarding policy for the unknown unicast packets. Options: 1. forward(1) -indicates that the unknown unicast packets are transparently transmitted. 2. discard(2) -indicates that the unknown unicast packets are discarded. During the creation of a VLAN, if this leaf is not specified, forward(1) is adopted by default. You can perform the set operation on this leaf to modify the VLAN-based forwarding policy for the unknown unicast packets. The VLAN-based forwarding policy for the unknown unicast packets can also be configured in hwPolicyUnknowncast of hwVlanSrvProfTable. If a VLAN service profile is bound to the VLAN, the configuration in the VLAN service profile takes effect.  Enumeration: 'forward': 1, 'discard': 2.

children.name: hwVlanOuterTpid
children.description: Indicates the Ethernet protocol type of a VLAN. Range: 1536-65535 (0x0600-0xFFFF) Default: 0x8100

children.name: hwVlanBindSrvProfName
children.description: Indicates the name of the VLAN service profile bound to a VLAN. Range: a string of 0-32 characters This leaf identifies a VLAN service profile, which must be created in hwVlanSrvProfTable. The null character string indicates that the binding relation between a VLAN and a VLAN service profile is deleted.

children.name: hwVlanChangeEnable
children.description: Indicates the operation type of whether a standard port list maps a VLAN. Options: 1. idle(0) -indicates invalid mapping. 2. addPort(1) -indicates that a port is added to the VLAN. 3. removePort(2) -indicates that a port is deleted from the VLAN. This leaf must work with hwVlanPorts.  Enumeration: 'idle': 0, 'addPort': 1, 'removePort': 2.

children.name: hwVlanBindRaioProfileName
children.description: Indicates the name of the RAIO profile bound to a VLAN. Range: a string of 0-32 characters This leaf identifies a RAIO profile, which must be created in hwDslamRAIOProfileTable. The null character string indicates that the binding relation between a VLAN and a RAIO profile is deleted.

children.name: hwVlanTrafficSuppressUnknowncastNetwork
children.description: Indicates the unknown unicast traffic suppression on a VLAN. Range: 0-13 Default: 0 13 indicates full-suppression of traffic, and 0 indicates no traffic suppression. The suppression levels and corresponding bandwidth ranges are listed as follows: --------------------------------------------------------------- NO. Min bandwidth(kbps) Max bandwidth(kbps) Package number(pps) --------------------------------------------------------------- 0 Not suppressed Not suppressed Not suppressed 1 6 145 12 2 12 291 24 3 24 582 48 4 48 1153 95 5 97 2319 191 6 195 4639 382 7 390 9265 763 8 781 18531 1526 9 1562 37063 3052 10 3125 74126 6104 11 6249 148241 12207 12 12499 296483 24414 13 0 0 0 ---------------------------------------------------------------

children.name: hwVlanMethL2Forward
children.description: Indicates the switch of MEth l2 forwarding on a VLAN. Options: 1. enable(1) -Enable MEth l2 forwarding on a VLAN. 2. disable(2) -Disable MEth l2 forwarding on a VLAN. The default value is disable(2).  Enumeration: 'enable': 1, 'disable': 2.

children.name: hwVlanInterfaceTable
children.description: Describes VLAN interface management, including IP address management, enabling and disabling of the DHCP client, and DHCP client option 60. The index of this table is hwVlanInterfaceID.

children.name: hwVlanInterfaceEntry
children.description: Describes VLAN interface management, including IP address management, enabling and disabling of the DHCP client, and DHCP client option 60. The index of this entry is hwVlanInterfaceID.

children.name: hwVlanInterfaceID
children.description: Indicates the index of a VLAN interface, which maps a VLAN ID. For example, the index of VLAN interface 3 is 3.

children.name: hwVlanID
children.description: Indicates the corresponding VLAN ID of a VLAN interface.

children.name: hwVlanIpAddress
children.description: Indicates the IP address of a VLAN interface. Default: 0.0.0.0.

children.name: hwVlanIpAddressMask
children.description: Indicates the IP address subnet mask.

children.name: hwVlanInterfaceAdminStatus
children.description: Indicates the management status of a VLAN interface. Options: 1. up(1) -indicates up status. 2. down(2) -indicates down status. Default: up(1)  Enumeration: 'down': 2, 'up': 1.

children.name: hwVlanInterfaceFrameType
children.description: Indicates the type of the frame that can be received by a VLAN interface. Options: 1. ethernetii(1) -For the frame format of ethernetii(1), see RFC894. 2. ethernetsnap(2) -The value is not supported. 3. ethernet8022(3) -The value is not supported. 4. ethernet8023(4) -The value is not supported. Currently, only ethernetii(1) is supported.  Enumeration: 'ethernet8023': 4, 'ethernet8022': 3, 'ethernetii': 1, 'ethernetsnap': 2.

children.name: hwInterfaceRowStatus
children.description: Indicates the row status. It is used for create, delete and modify operations. Options: 1. createAndGo(4) 2. destroy(6) 3. active(1)

children.name: hwVlanInterfaceLinkStatus
children.description: Indicates the protocol status of a link that is contained in a VLAN interface. Options: 1. up(1) -The protocol status of a link that is contained in a VLAN interface is up. 2. down(2) -The protocol status of a link that is contained in a VLAN interface is down.  Enumeration: 'down': 2, 'up': 1.

children.name: hwVlanIfIPMode
children.description: Indicates the mode of obtaining an IP address. Options: 1. static(1) -Configured statically. 2. dhcp(2) -Obtained through DHCP.  Enumeration: 'dhcp': 2, 'static': 1.

children.name: hwVlanIfDhcpClientOption60
children.description: Indicates the option 60 information carried in DHCP packets that are sent by a L3 interface when obtaining an IP address in the DHCP mode. Range: 0-32 characters

children.name: hwVlanIfVlanEncapMode
children.description: Used to configure the VLAN encapsulation mode of a VLAN interface. Options: 1. singleTag(1) -Single tag VLAN encapsulation mode. 2. doubleTag(2) -Double tag VLAN encapsulation mode. Default: singleTag(1)  Enumeration: 'doubleTag': 2, 'singleTag': 1.

children.name: hwVlanIfVlanInnerLabel
children.description: Used to configure the inner VLAN ID when the VLAN encapsulation mode of a VLAN interface is double-tag mode. Range: 1-4095 Default: 1

children.name: hwVlanIfDHCPSStatus
children.description: Describes the mode of dhcp server on this interface. Options: 1. disable(1) -disable dhcp server. 2. enable(2) -enable dhcp server. Default: disable(1)  Enumeration: 'enable': 2, 'disable': 1.

children.name: hwIPv6MTU
children.description: Used to configure the maximum transmission unit of vlanif.If you set it on one vlanif,all the vlanif will be configured. For P300 device, the node can take effect on IPV4 and IPV6. For Saturn device, it only takes effect on IPV6. Range: -1,1280-1499,1501-1560. For P300 device, the range is -1,1501-1560. For Saturn device, the range is -1,1280-1499,1501-1560. Deafult:-1,this value means the MTU of vlanif is the default value(for example: 1500).

children.name: hwIPv4MTU
children.description: Used to configure the maximum transmission unit of vlanif. The node is only supported on Saturn device. It only takes effect on IPV4. Range: -1,1501-1560 Deafult:-1,this value means the MTU of vlanif is the default value(for example: 1500).

children.name: hwifSVLANVlanListTable
children.description: Indicates the super VLAN list, shows the sub VLANs in the super VLAN. The index of this table is hwifSvlanVlanID.

children.name: hwifSVLANVlanListEntry
children.description: Indicates the super VLAN list, shows the sub VLANs in the super VLAN. The index of this entry is hwifSvlanVlanID.

children.name: hwifSvlanVlanID
children.description: The index of the table, indicates the super VLAN ID

children.name: hwifSvlanSubVlanlistLow
children.description: The low oct string for sub VLAN list of Primary VLANs, Each bit is one VLAN. All bits be 2048(256 * 8) VLAN. Sub VLAN will be added to super VLAN.

children.name: hwifSvlanSubVlanlisHigh
children.description: The high oct string for sub VLAN list of Primary VLANs, Each bit is one VLAN. All bits be 2048(256 * 8) VLAN Sub VLAN will be added to super VLAN.

children.name: hwifSvlanOperStatus
children.description: VLAN operational status, now support createAndGo(4),destroy(6)

children.name: hwifPVLANMappingTable
children.description: Secondary VLAN lists of Primary VLANs. The index of this table is hwifPvlanPrimaryVlanID.

children.name: hwifPVLANMappingEntry
children.description: Secondary VLAN lists of Primary VLANs. The index of this entry is hwifPvlanPrimaryVlanID.

children.name: hwifPvlanPrimaryVlanID
children.description: Primary VLAN ID

children.name: hwifPvlanSecondaryVlanlistLow
children.description: The second low oct string for sub VLAN list of Primary VLANs, Each bit is one VLAN. All bits be 2048(256 * 8) VLAN Secondary VLAN will be added to primary VLAN.

children.name: hwifPvlanSecondaryVlanlistHigh
children.description: The second low oct string for sub VLAN list of Primary VLANs, Each bit is one VLAN. All bits be 2048(256 * 8) VLAN Secondary VLAN will be added to primary VLAN.

children.name: hwifPvlanOperStatus
children.description: vlan operational status, now support createAndGo(4),destroy(6)

children.name: hwRegionVLanTable
children.description: Indicates the region VLAN, it is used to configure the region VLAN. The index of this table is hwVlanIndex.

children.name: hwRegionVLanEntry
children.description: Indicates the region VLAN, it is used to configure the region VLAN. The index of this entry is hwVlanIndex.

children.name: hwRegionVpi
children.description: THE atm vpi of the VLAN.

children.name: hwRegionVci
children.description: The atm vci of the VLAN.

children.name: hwRegionPVCRowStatus
children.description: Row status,now support createAndGo(4),destroy(6). 4 is used for creating group pvc for region VLAN, 6 is used for deleting group pvc for region VLAN.

children.name: hwSmartVLanTable
children.description: Indicates the smart VLAN, it is used to configure the smart VLAN. The index of this table is hwSmartVlanID.

children.name: hwSmartVLanEntry
children.description: Indicates the smart VLAN, it is used to configure the smart VLAN. The index of this entry is hwSmartVlanID.

children.name: hwSmartVlanID
children.description: The index of the table, indicates a smart VLAN ID.

children.name: hwSmartVlanUplinkPort
children.description: smart VLAN uplink ports

children.name: hwSmartVlanDownlinkPort
children.description: smart VLAN downlink ports

children.name: hwSmartVlanRowStatus
children.description: Row status, now support createAndGo(4),destroy(6)

children.name: hwMuxVlanEnable
children.description: Enable/disable MUX VLAN. Options: 1. enabled(1) -Enable MUX VLAN. 2. disabled(2) -Disable MUX VLAN.  Enumeration: 'disabled': 2, 'enabled': 1.

children.name: hwMuxVlanPortConfTable
children.description: Indicates the Mux VLAN port configuration, it is used to configure the Mux VLAN port. The index of this table is ifIndex.

children.name: hwMuxVlanPortConfEntry
children.description: Indicates the Mux VLAN port configuration, it is used to configure the Mux VLAN port. The index of this entry is ifIndex.

children.name: hwMuxVlanPortType
children.description: Configure the uplink-port or cascading-port for the MUX VLAN. Options: 1. uplinkPort(1) -uplink port 2. cascadingPort(2) -cascading port  Enumeration: 'uplinkPort': 1, 'cascadingPort': 2.

children.name: hwMuxVlanStartVlanId
children.description: The start VLAN ID of Mux VLAN.

children.name: hwMuxVlanGroupNum
children.description: The VLAN group number.

children.name: hwMuxVlanPortConfRowStatus
children.description: Row status, now support createAndGo(4),destroy(6).

children.name: hwMuxVlanUplinkPort
children.description: Uplink port for mux VLAN configuration.(for UA 5000)

children.name: hwMuxVlanDownlinkPort
children.description: Downlink port for mux VLAN configuration. If the value is -1, use inner port instead(Only used for UA5000).

children.name: hwMuxVlanSlotConfTable
children.description: Indicates the I/O board MUX VLAN configure, it is used to configure the I/O board MUX VLAN. The index of this table is hwSlotIndex.

children.name: hwMuxVlanSlotConfEntry
children.description: Indicates the I/O board MUX VLAN configure, it is used to configure the I/O board MUX VLAN. The index of this entry is hwSlotIndex.

children.name: hwMuxVlanSlotStartVlanId
children.description: The start VLAN ID for the I/O board.

children.name: hwMuxVlanSlotRowStatus
children.description: Row status, now support createAndGo(4),destroy(6).

children.name: hwMultiVLanTable
children.description: Indicates the Multi VLAN, it is used to configure the multi VLAN. The index of this table is hwMultiVlanID.

children.name: hwMultiVLanEntry
children.description: Indicates the Multi VLAN, it is used to configure the multi VLAN. The index of this entry is hwMultiVlanID.

children.name: hwMultiVlanID
children.description: The index of the table, indicates a Multi VLAN ID.

children.name: hwMultiVlanUplinkPort
children.description: Multi VLAN uplink ports.

children.name: hwMultiVlanDownlinkPort
children.description: Multi VLAN downlink ports.

children.name: hwMultiVlanRowStatus
children.description: Row status, now support createAndGo(4),destroy(6).

children.name: hwVlanAggregationTable
children.description: Describes the relation between the super VLAN and the sub VLAN in a VLAN aggregation. The indexes of this table are hwVlanAggregationSuperVlanId and hwVlanAggregationSubVlanId.

children.name: hwVlanAggregationEntry
children.description: Describes the relation between the super VLAN and the sub VLAN in a VLAN aggregation. The indexes of this entry are hwVlanAggregationSuperVlanId and hwVlanAggregationSubVlanId.

children.name: hwVlanAggregationSuperVlanId
children.description: Indicates the super VLAN ID in a VLAN aggregation. Range: 2-4093

children.name: hwVlanAggregationSubVlanId
children.description: Indicates the sub VLAN ID in a VLAN aggregation. Range: 2-4093

children.name: hwVlanAggregationSubVlanArpProxyStatus
children.description: Indicates the status of ARP proxy in a sub VLAN. Options: 1. enabled(1) -Enable ARP proxy in a sub VLAN. 2. disabled(2) -Disable ARP proxy in a sub VLAN. Default: disabled(2)  Enumeration: 'disabled': 2, 'enabled': 1.

children.name: hwVlanAggregationRowStatus
children.description: Indicates the row status, used for creating or deleting a VLAN aggregation. Options: 1. active(1) 2. createAndGo(4) 3. destroy(6) To create a VLAN aggregation, specify the indexes, and set hwVlanAggregationRowStatus to createAndGo(4) to perform the set operation. To delete a VLAN aggregation, specify the indexes, and set hwVlanAggregationRowStatus to destroy(6) to perform the set operation. During query, the value of this leaf is the fixed active(1).

children.name: hwVlanAggregationSubVlanNdProxyStatus
children.description: Indicates the status of ND proxy in a sub VLAN. Options: 1. enabled(1) -Enable ND proxy in a sub VLAN. 2. disabled(2) -Disable ND proxy in a sub VLAN. Default: disabled(2)  Enumeration: 'disabled': 2, 'enabled': 1.

children.name: hwStackingVlanInnerEthernetType
children.description: Indicates the Ethernet protocol type of the inner VLAN tag supported by VLAN stacking. Range: 0-65535 Default: 0x8100

children.name: hwVlanFlowAccountTable
children.description: Describes the VLAN-based traffic statistics, including the numbers of the upstream bytes, downstream bytes, upstream packets, downstream packets, upstream and downstream packets in the ACL-based traffic statistics collection, discarded upstream packets, and discarded downstream packets. The indexes of this table are hwVlanIndex (outer VLAN ID) and hwInnerVlanID (inner VLAN ID). hwVlanIndex references the leaf in hwVlanMIBTable. If hwInnerVlanID is -1, that means the InnerVLAN-based traffic statistics is not supported. If hwVlanTrafficOccupiedTable is being used to query the traffic and bandwidth occupancy of a VLAN, querying hwVlanFlowAccountTable fails.

children.name: hwVlanFlowAccountEntry
children.description: Describes the VLAN-based traffic statistics, including the numbers of the upstream bytes, downstream bytes, upstream packets, downstream packets, upstream and downstream packets in the ACL-based traffic statistics collection, discarded upstream packets, and discarded downstream packets. The indexes of this entry are hwVlanIndex (outer VLAN ID) and hwInnerVlanID (inner VLAN ID). hwVlanIndex references the leaf in hwVlanMIBTable. If hwInnerVlanID is -1, that means the InnerVLAN-based traffic statistics is not supported. If hwVlanTrafficOccupiedTable is being used to query the traffic and bandwidth occupancy of a VLAN, querying hwVlanFlowAccountTable fails.

children.name: hwInnerVlanID
children.description: Indicates the inner VLAN tag in a stacking VLAN. If the VLAN is not of the stacking attribute or you perform the query operation only by the outer VLAN, this leaf must be set to -1. Currently, ACL-based VLAN traffic statistics of only the outer VLAN can be collected. Therefore, this value of this leaf is not useful, and you'd better set the value to -1. 0 is not supported.

children.name: hwUpFlowAccountByte
children.description: Indicates the number of upstream bytes of a VLAN. '18446744073709551615' means invalid value.

children.name: hwDownFlowAccountByte
children.description: Indicates the number of downstream bytes of a VLAN. '18446744073709551615' means invalid value.

children.name: hwUpFlowAccountPacket
children.description: Indicates the number of upstream packets of a VLAN. '18446744073709551615' means invalid value.

children.name: hwDownFlowAccountPacket
children.description: Indicates the number of downstream packets of a VLAN. '18446744073709551615' means invalid value.

children.name: hwUpStreamPacket
children.description: Indicates the number of upstream packets in the ACL-based VLAN traffic statistics collection. After the first query, 0 is fixedly returned. After the second query, traffic statistics of the VLAN between the two queries are returned. If the query or delete operation is not performed on the traffic statistics of this VLAN within 10 minutes, the traffic statistics collection of the VLAN is invalid. If a new index is specified in the second query, the traffic statistics of the new VLAN are collected. The system can collect the traffic statistics of a maximum of 64 VLANs concurrently. '18446744073709551615' means invalid value.

children.name: hwDownStreamPacket
children.description: Indicates the number of downstream packets in the ACL-based VLAN traffic statistics collection. After the first query, 0 is fixedly returned. After the second query, traffic statistics of the VLAN between the two queries are returned. If the query or delete operation is not performed on the traffic statistics of this VLAN within 10 minutes, the traffic statistics collection of the VLAN is invalid. If a new index is specified in the second query, the traffic statistics of the new VLAN are collected. The system can collect the traffic statistics of a maximum of 64 VLANs concurrently. '18446744073709551615' means invalid value.

children.name: hwFlowAccountAdminStatus
children.description: Used to delete the VLAN traffic statistics. Options: 1. invalid(-1) -During the query, the invalid value -1 is fixedly returned. 2. reset(0) -indicates that the VLAN traffic statistics based on service board are deleted. 3. resetAcl(1) -indicates that the VLAN traffic statistics based on ACL are deleted.  Enumeration: 'reset': 0, 'invalid': -1, 'resetAcl': 1.

children.name: hwUpFlowAccountDiscardPacket
children.description: Indicates the number of upstream discarded packets of a VLAN. '18446744073709551615' means invalid value.

children.name: hwDownFlowAccountDiscardPacket
children.description: Indicates the number of downstream discarded packets of a VLAN. '18446744073709551615' means invalid value.

children.name: hwVlanUpCarTable
children.description: Indicates the VLAN up direct CAR. The index of this table is hwVlanUpCarId.

children.name: hwVlanUpCarEntry
children.description: Indicates the VLAN up direct CAR. The index of this entry is hwVlanUpCarId.

children.name: hwVlanUpCarId
children.description: The index of the table, indicates a up direct Carid.

children.name: hwVlanUpCarName
children.description: Up direct car name.

children.name: hwVlanUpCarBandValue
children.description: Car band value,The car value is multiple of 64kbps. Unit :kbps

children.name: hwVlanUpCarBurstValue
children.description: Car burst value. Unit:kbps

children.name: hwVlanUpCarIsUsed
children.description: The flag indicates whether the carid is used. Options: 1. used(1) -The carid is used. 2. noUsed(2) -The carid is no-used.  Enumeration: 'used': 1, 'noUsed': 2.

children.name: hwVlanUpCarRowStatus
children.description: Row status, now support createAndGo(4),destroy(6).

children.name: hwVlanDownCarTable
children.description: Indicates the VLAN down direct CAR. The index of this table is hwVlanDownCarId.

children.name: hwVlanDownCarEntry
children.description: Indicates the VLAN down direct CAR. The index of this entry is hwVlanDownCarId.

children.name: hwVlanDownCarId
children.description: The index of the table, indicates a down direct carid.

children.name: hwVlanDownCarName
children.description: Down direct car name.

children.name: hwVlanDownCarBandValue
children.description: Car band value,The car value is multiple of 64kbps. Unit: kbps

children.name: hwVlanDownCarBurstValue
children.description: Car burst value. Unit: kbps

children.name: hwVlanDownCarIsUsed
children.description: The flag indicates whether the carid is used. Options: 1. used(1) -The carid is used. 2. noUsed(2) -The carid is no-used.  Enumeration: 'used': 1, 'noUsed': 2.

children.name: hwVlanDownCarRowStatus
children.description: Row status, now support createAndGo(4),destroy(6).

children.name: hwVlanParaTable
children.description: Indicates the VLAN parameters, include hwVlanParaIndex, hwVlanMacLearnCpability, hwVlanMaxMacLearnNum, hwVlanUpdirectCar, hwVlanDownDirectCar, it is used to configure the VLAN param. The index of this table is hwVlanParamIndex.

children.name: hwVlanParaEntry
children.description: Indicates the VLAN parameters, include hwVlanParaIndex, hwVlanMacLearnCpability, hwVlanMaxMacLearnNum, hwVlanUpdirectCar, hwVlanDownDirectCar, it is used to configure the VLAN param. The index of this entry is hwVlanParamIndex.

children.name: hwVlanParaIndex
children.description: The index of the table,the VLAN index means Vlan Id.

children.name: hwVlanMacLearnCpability
children.description: MAC learning or not flag by VLAN. Options: 1. enabled(1) -Enable MAC learning by VLAN. 2. disabled(2) -Disable MAC learning by VLAN.  Enumeration: 'disabled': 2, 'enabled': 1.

children.name: hwVlanMaxMacLearnNum
children.description: The VLAN max mac learn number.

children.name: hwVlanUpDirectCarID

children.name: hwBpduTunnelTable

children.name: hwBpduTunnelEntry
children.description: Used for setting and querying the status of the L2 transparent transmission of BPDU packets. The index of this entry is hwVlanIndex.

children.name: hwBpduTunnel
children.description: Indicates the status of the L2 transparent transmission of BDPU packets in a VLAN. Options: 1. enable(1) -Enable transparent transmission of BDPU packets in a VLAN. 2. disable(2) -Disable transparent transmission of BDPU packets in a VLAN. Default: disable(2)  Enumeration: 'enable': 1, 'disable': 2.

children.name: hwVOIPAddressTable
children.description: VOIP multiply IP table. The index of this table is hwVOIPAddressIndex

children.name: hwVOIPAddressEntry
children.description: VOIP multiply IP table. The index of this entry is hwVOIPAddressIndex

children.name: hwVOIPAddressIndex
children.description: the index scope is 0-63

children.name: hwVOIPIPType
children.description: Indicates the type of VOIP IP. Options: 1. media(1) -indicates that the type of VOIP IP is media. 2. signaling(2) -indicates that the type of VOIP IP is signaling.  Enumeration: 'media': 1, 'signaling': 2.

children.name: hwVOIPIPAddress
children.description: IP address

children.name: hwVOIPSubMask

children.name: hwVOIPQosIPStrategy
children.description: Indicates the qos ip strategy Options: 1. tos(1) -indicates that the qos ip strategy is tos. 2. dscp(2) -indicates that the qos ip strategy is dscp. Enumeration: 'tos': 1, 'dscp': 2.

children.name: hwVOIPAddressRowStatus
children.description: Indicates the status of this conceptual row. Options: 1. active(1) 2. createAndGo(4) 3. destroy(6) Until instances of all corresponding columns are appropriately configured, the value of the corresponding instance of the hwAddressRowStatus column is 'notReady'.

children.name: hwVOIPAddressObtainMode
children.description: ip address obtain mode: Options: 1. static(1) -static config 2. pppoe(2) -pppoe dynamic obtain 3. dhcp(3) -dhcp dynamic obtain  Enumeration: 'dhcp': 3, 'static': 1, 'pppoe': 2.

children.name: hwVOIPPPPOEClientName
children.description: ip address name of pppoe dynamic obtain, the same as pppoe client name

children.name: hwVOIPIPAddressSrc
children.description: Indicates the source type of IP. Options: 1. static(0) -indicates that the source type of IP is static. 2. dhcp(1) -indicates that the source type of IP is dhcp.  Enumeration: 'dhcp': 1, 'static': 0.

children.name: hwVOIPQosTable
children.description: Describes the Qos IP tos and VLAN priority The index of this table is hwVOIPAddressIndex

children.name: hwVOIPQosEntry
children.description: Describes the Qos IP tos and VLAN priority The index of this entry is hwVOIPAddressIndex
