children.description: The agent generates this trap when the batteries recover.

children.name: hwPowerModuleMismatchTrap
children.description: The agent generates this trap when the the power supply system detects mismatched power module .

children.name: hwPowerModuleRestoreTrap
children.description: The agent generates this trap when the power module recovers.

children.name: hwDev
children.description: huawei device mib.

children.name: hwSysIpAddr
children.description: IP address of the system,IP address of the net port used for device maintenance.It'd better not to modify this address when out-band NMS is used.

children.name: hwSysIpMask
children.description: IP address mask of the system. IP address of the net port used for device maintenance. It'd be better not to IP address mask together with address mask. It will take no effect to separately configure IP address or address mask. It'd when out-band NMS is used.

children.name: hwSysVersion
children.description: The System Version is consistent with the specification of HUAWEI product. For example, MD5500 V100R001M30B01PXXXX.

children.name: hwSysTime
children.description: The current date and time of the system.

children.name: hwNmsParaEntry
children.description: NMS parameters configuration table entity.

children.name: hwNmsIndex
children.description: Index(1..32),at most supports 32 NMSs,exclusively identifies a NMS.

children.name: hwNmsName
children.description: Name of the NMS, which des not have to be consistent with that of the NMS workstation.

children.name: hwNmsIp
children.description: IP address of the NMS workstation that can be outband or inband address.

children.name: hwNmsMask
children.description: IP address mask of the NMS workstation.

children.name: hwNmsMaintainMode
children.description: Maintenance mode of NMS workstation,if the IP address of the NMS station is in-band, the mode must also be in-band.  Enumeration: 'outBandwidth': 2, 'inBandwidth': 1.

children.name: hwNmsGetCommunity
children.description: Community authentication name used for SNMP protocol GET operation, default value: public.

children.name: hwNmsSetCommunity
children.description: Community authentication name used for SNMP protocol SET operation, default value: private.

children.name: hwNmsSnmpPort
children.description: Snmp communication port of NMS workstation,default value:161.

children.name: hwNmsTrapPort
children.description: Trap receive Port of NMS workstation, default value:162.

children.name: hwNmsClass
children.description: Class of NMS station,default value is 3.  Enumeration: 'ro': 1, 'rw': 2, 'rwWithTrap': 3, 'trapOnly': 4.

children.name: hwNmsStatus
children.description: Operation status of NMS station,the NMS station can be added,deleted and modified.

children.name: hwFrameTable
children.description: Frame description table that describes basic information of a frame. It includes the frame type, the number of slots in the frame, etc. The number of slots vary with the type of the frame where it is located. For example,, there are has 16 slots in MA5100 while 4 ones in MA5103. This table is also adopted for the case-shaped device with Agent (For example, the MA5105). There is no frame in this his kind of device. Thus, the device can be put on the rack with other ones during implementation. Its frame index is specified as 0. The frame type is imported from the relevant definition of the HW-TC table.

children.name: hwFrameEntry
children.description: Frame description table entity.

children.name: hwFrameIndex
children.description: Frame Index,the number of the frame in the device. This table is also adopted by the case-shaped device with Agent (For example, the MA5105). There is no frame in this kind of device. Thus it is placed on the rack with other devices During implementation. The frame index is specified as 0.

children.name: hwFrameType
children.description: Frame type,one kind of the frame types defined in HW-TC table. According to the private MIB standard of the company, the product must support read-only mode. In other words, you can query the frame type the NMS. You can choose for various broadband product to support read-write mode for the dynamic control of frame type.

children.name: hwFrameDesc
children.description: Frame description, the maximum length of the character string is 64. This table is used to describe some extra information. For example, to facilitate management, use it to describe the frame that is located in XX frame XX apparatus room.

children.name: hwSlots
children.description: Slot number of the frame, refers to the physical slot number of the frame, which depends on the frame type and has nothing to do with the number of boards placed in the slots, whose number varies with the frame type. For example, there are 16 slots in MA5100 while 4 lots in MA5103.

children.name: hwFrameOperStatus
children.description: Frame operation status. This variable is used to indicate whether the frame works in a normal status.  Enumeration: 'fault': 2, 'other': 3, 'discovery': 4, 'normal': 1.

children.name: hwFrameAdminStatus
children.description: Frame administration status. It only describes the statuses in common use, including  Enumeration: 'reset': 3, 'enable': 2, 'confirm': 5, 'disable': 1, 'test': 4, 'delete': 6.

children.name: hwFrameRowStatus
children.description: Row status of the frame:mainly to support the offline configuration of addition and deletion. You can choose for various broadband products to support this function.Row status is used to manage the creation or deletion of the concept rows.The following shows six statuses.

children.name: hwSlotTable
children.description: Slot description table, which describes detailed information of all boards in each slot which is on the frame, including the number of subslots, the status of the board, the software of the board, the hardware version No., the working mode of the board, etc. This table must be implemented.

children.name: hwSlotEntry
children.description: Slot description table entity.

children.name: hwSlotIndex
children.description: Slot index that identifies the physical position of a slot. The case-shaped device is treated as the one with only one slot whose index is always set as 0. If there are ports in the frame, all the ports on the frame must be virtualized as a fixed slot index (equal to the virtual slots which is the max slot index for the frame plus 1.) Their slot index is also fixedly set as 0.

children.name: hwSlotType
children.description: Board type. The board type defined in HW-TC table is recommended. According to the private MIB standard of the company, all the products must support the read-only mode. In other words, you can query the slot type through the NMS. You can choose for various broadband products to support the read-write mode for the dynamic control of slot type.

children.name: hwSlotDesc
children.description: Slot information description, used to describe extra information of the board. For example, it can be adopted for a user access device to describe the information of a user group connected to the slot.

children.name: hwSlotPcbVersion
children.description: The PCB version information of the slot. It has been discarded in the fixed net MIB. The information of PCB version and other versions are described in the hwSlotVersion.

children.name: hwSlotVersion
children.description:
Board version information. Refer to the technical specifications of Huawei Technologies Co., Ltd. Use the new-line character 
 (ACSII 0x0A) to space various version information.If there is no corresponding version, the new-line character shall also be inserted to remain the order. Detailed order information: Hardware PCB version 
 Software version 
 Logic version 
 DSP version 
 Standby CPU software version 
 Chip version 
 Other software version of the chip with a software 
 Other version information

children.name: hwSlotWorkMode
children.description: Board working mode that describes whether the board is working in main state or in standby state.  Enumeration: 'standby': 2, 'main': 1, 'other': 255.

children.name: hwSubSlots
children.description: The number of the subslots. The subslot is used to plug the subboard in the board. The number subslots can be determined when the board's been made, whether the subboard has been inserted in the subslot.

children.name: hwSlotOperStatus
children.description: Operation status of the board.  Enumeration: 'normal': 2, 'fault': 3, 'forbidden': 4, 'abnormal': 8, 'offline': 7, 'uninstall': 1, 'config': 6, 'discovery': 5.

children.name: hwSlotAdminStatus
children.description: Administration status of the board.  Enumeration: 'reset': 3, 'enable': 2, 'confirm': 5, 'forbidden': 8, 'switch': 6, 'disable': 1, 'test': 4, 'unforbidden': 9, 'delete': 7.

children.name: hwSlotRowStatus
children.description: Row status:mainly to support the offline configuration of board addition and deletion. Various broadband products can be determined whether to support this function.

children.name: hwSlotPhySerialNum
children.description: The vendor-specific serial number string for the physical entity. The preferred value is the serial number string actually printed on the component itself (if present).

children.name: hwSubslotTable
children.description: Subslot description table that describes detailed information of each subslot attached to the board.

children.name: hwSubslotEntry
children.description: Subslot description table entity.

children.name: hwSubslotIndex
children.description: Subslot Index. The present subslot index is determined by its physical position in the board.

children.name: hwSubslotType
children.description: Subboard type in the subslot,refer to HW-TC table. According to the private MIB standard of the company, the product must support read-only mode. In other words, you can query the subboard type through the NMS. You can choose for various broadband product to support read-write mode for the dynamic control of frame type.

children.name: hwSubslotPorts
children.description: The number of physical ports owned by the subboard in the subslot.

children.name: hwSubslotOperStatus
children.description: Operation status of the subboard in the subslot.  Enumeration: 'fault': 3, 'forbidden': 4, 'normal': 2, 'uninstall': 1.

children.name: hwSubslotAdminStatus
children.description: Administration status of the subboard in the subslot. The following only describes some statuses in common use. If there are some other statuses, just extend them. delete(6) - discard this node through hwSubSlotRowStatus.  Enumeration: 'reset': 3, 'enable': 2, 'confirm': 5, 'disable': 1, 'test': 4, 'delete': 6.

children.name: hwSubslotVersion
children.description: Subboard version information. Refer to the technical specifications of Huawei Technologies Co., Ltd. Use the new-line character \n (ACSII 0x0A) to space various version information.

children.name: hwSubSlotDesc
children.description: Subboard description.

children.name: hwSubslotRowStatus
children.description: Row status:mainly to support the offline configuration of subboard addition and deletion.Each product can determine whether to offer this kind of function.

children.name: hwPortTable
children.description: Port configuration table that describes the detailed information of physical ports in the board, including the type, status and rate of the port.This table must be implemented.

children.name: hwPortEntry
children.description: Port configuration table entity.

children.name: hwPortIndex
children.description: Port index, the index of this table, which exclusively determines all the ports in a subboard.

children.name: hwPortType
children.description: Port type. According to the private MIB standard of the company, the product must support read-only mode. In other words, you can query the frame type through the NMS. You can choose for various broadband product to support read-write mode for the dynamic control of subboard type.

children.name: hwPortDesc
children.description: Port description, used to describe extra information of the port. For example, for a user access device it can be adopted to describe the information of the user who is connecting to the port.

children.name: hwPortSpeed
children.description: The speed of this port.

children.name: hwPortOperStatus
children.description: Port operation status.  Enumeration: 'remoteLoopback': 6, 'nolight': 13, 'normal': 1, 'fault': 2, 'forbidden': 4, 'activing': 10, 'innerRemoteLoopback': 15, 'innerLocalLoopback': 14, 'test': 5, 'deactive': 11, 'block': 12, 'localLoopback': 3.

children.name: hwPortAdminStatus
children.description: Port administration status.  Enumeration: 'reset': 7, 'remoteLoopback': 9, 'confirm': 5, 'rtuRemoteLoopback': 15, 'innerRemoteLoopback': 13, 'innerLocalLoopback': 12, 'rtuLocalLoopback': 14, 'unblock': 4, 'stopLoopback': 11, 'localLoopback': 8, 'active': 1, 'deactive': 2, 'block': 3, 'delete': 6.

children.name: hwFrameLinkNumber
children.description: Number of frame Links, which refers to the number of links between the main frame and the standby frame of the presen device. If there are many frames, but the device cannot know the link relation of the frames, then the initial value of this node is 0. If a user manually adds the link between the frames later, then this node shall be renewed.

children.name: hwFrameLinkTable
children.description: The frame link table. It describes the topology relation between the frames. For the device that can automatically discover the link relationship between the devices, this table can be implemented as read-only table. For the device whose inter-frame relation needs to be configured manually, this table shall support adding and deletion. All the links must locate on the two existing ports.

children.name: hwFrameLinkEntry
children.description: The entry of the frame link table. There are the left and right node for a frame link. Each node is in the form of frame ID + slot ID + subslot + port.

children.name: hwFrameLinkIndex
children.description: Index of the frame link. It is sequentially numerated and exclusively identified in the device. There is no restriction to the coding rule.

children.name: hwFrameLinkLeftFrame
children.description: The ID of the left node linked to the frame, corresponding to the hwFrameIndex in the hwFrameTable

children.name: hwFrameLinkLeftSlot
children.description: The ID of the left slot linked to the frame, corresponding to the hwSlotIndex in the hwSlotTable. It indicates which slot of the left node is the link entry.

children.name: hwFrameLinkLeftSubSlot
children.description: Link the left subslot, corresponding to the hwSubSlotIndex in the hwSubTable. It indicates which subslot of the left node is the link entry.

children.name: hwFrameLinkLeftPort
children.description: The ID of the left port linked to the frame, corresponding to the hwPortIndex in the hwPortTable. It indicates which port of the left node is the link entry.

children.name: hwFrameLinkRightFrame
children.description: The ID of the right node linked to the frame, corresponding to the hwFrameIndex of the hwFrameTable.

children.name: hwFrameLinkRightSlot
children.description: The ID of the right slot linked the frame, corresponding to the hwSlotIndex of the hwSlotTable. It indicates which slot of the right node is the link entry.

children.name: hwFrameLinkRightSubSlot
children.description: Link the right subslot, corresponding to the hwSubSlotIndex in the hwSubSlotTable. It indicates which subslot of the right node is the link entry.

children.name: hwFrameLinkRightPort
children.description: The ID of the right port linked to the frame, corresponding to the hwPortIndex in the hwPortTable. It indicates which port of the right port is the link entry.

children.name: hwFrameLinkOperStatus
children.description: The running status of the link  Enumeration: 'fault': 2, 'unknown': 3, 'normal': 1.

children.name: hwFrameLinkRowStatus
children.description: The row status of the frame link, used to add or delete a link.

children.name: hwFrameLinkNextIndex
children.description: The frame link table indicates adding the index value to be assigned by the new link. This leaf is used to access an index ID of the next frame link dynamically assigned by the host before delivering the adding link. To deliver the adding link, the value of the leaf shall be accessed, and be delivered together with the 'frame link table'. Otherwise, the host can not execute the operation and will return the error.

children.name: hwBoardAttrTable
children.description: Inquiring or modifying A_ULaw, impedance and current of ASL, A32 and H511POTS ports.

children.name: hwBoardAttrEntry
children.description: Narrow board attribute table entity

children.name: hwBoardAulaw
children.description: Coding method of voice signal when digitalizing. In different country or area it should be A law or u law. 1 -- A law 2 -- ulaw

children.name: hwBoardCurrent
children.description: Port current supported by the board. The value ranges from 1 to 8, which indicates the port current value supported under certain loopline impedence. 1 -- 25mA steady current 2 -- 16mA steady current 3 -- 35mA 2*200 ohm 4 -- 35mA 2*250 ohm 5 -- 35mA 2*400 ohm 6 -- 47mA 2*200 ohm 7 -- 47mA 2*250 ohm 8 -- 47mA 2*400 ohm

children.name: hwBoardImpedance
children.description: Port impedance of the board. The following values indicates different impedance with different application circumstances. 1 -- Bureau machine in China(200+680|| 100nf) 2 -- User Machine in China(200+560|| 100nf) 3 -- 600 ohm Interface 4 -- Interface of russian(150+510|| 47nf) 5 -- (220+820|| 115nf ) 6 -- (220+820|| 120nf ) 7 -- 900 ohm Interface 8 -- Interface of Brazil(800|| 50nf) 255 -- Private definition

children.name: hwCpuDevTable
children.description: This table provides the information of CPU usage statistics of device in the period of last 5 seconds, 1 minute,or 5 minutes.

children.name: hwCpuDevEntry
children.description: The Entries of hwCpuDevTable. The hwCpuDevTable is indexed by hwFrameIndex, hwSlotIndex and hwCpuDevIndex. hwFrameIndex - the index of frame of the device. for example, hwFrameIndex equals 0 in NE16. hwSlotIndex - the slot number of the device, the MAX value varies with different devices. hwCpuDevIndex - for the purpose of extension.In single CPU devices (NE16,eg.), hwCpuDevIndex equals 0.

children.name: hwCpuDevIndex
children.description: The object is used only for the purpose of extension. For single-CPU devices, the value of this object equals 0.

children.name: hwCpuDevDuty
children.description: The value of this object identifies the average CPU occupancy of a board or an entity.

children.name: hwAvgDuty1min
children.description: The value of this object identifies the average CPU occupancy of a board or an entity in the last one minute before you access the object.

children.name: hwAvgDuty5min
children.description: The value of this object identifies the average CPU occupancy of a board or an entity in the last five minutes before you access the object.

children.name: hwMemoryDev
children.description: This mib module defines the memory information. NMS can query memory utilization statistics from device by the mib.

children.name: hwMemoryDevTable
children.description: This table provides the information of all memory utilization statistics of device. It contains the total size, the free size, the used size, and so on.

children.name: hwMemoryDevEntry
children.description: The Entries of hwMemoryDevTable. The table is indexed by hwFrameIndex, hwSlotIndex and hwMemoryDevModuleIndex, hwFrameIndex - the index of frame of the device. for example, hwFrameIndex equals 0 in NE16. hwSlotIndex - the slot number of the device, the MAX value varies with different devices. hwMemoryDevModuleIndex - for the purpose of extension.In single CPU devices (NE16,eg.), its value equals 0.

children.name: hwMemoryDevModuleIndex
children.description: The object is used only for the purpose of extension,In single CPU devices (NE16,eg.), hwMemoryDevModuleIndex equals 0.

children.name: hwMemoryDevSize
children.description: The object indicates the total size of the memory in bytes, which is on the managed object.

children.name: hwMemoryDevFree
children.description: The object indicates the free size of the memory in bytes.

children.name: hwMemoryDevRawSliceUsed
children.description: The object indicates the used size of the raw slice memory in bytes.

children.name: hwMemoryDevLargestFree
children.description: The object indicates the largest number of contiguous bytes from the memory that are currently unused on the managed object.

children.name: hwMemoryDevFail
children.description: The object indicates the count of memory allocation failures.

children.name: hwMemoryDevFailNoMem
children.description: The object indicates the count of memory allocation failures due to no free memory.

children.name: hwBufferTable
children.description: This table provides the inquiry of buffer utilization statistics of device. The type of the buffer is classified by size: 32 bytes, 64 bytes,...,etc.

children.name: hwBufferEntry
children.description: The Entries of hwBufferTable. The hwBufferTable is indexed by hwFrameIndex, hwSlotIndex, hwBufferModuleIndex and hwBufferSize. hwFrameIndex - the index of frame of the device. for example, hwFrameIndex equals 0 in NE16. hwSlotIndex - the slot number of the device, the MAX value varies with different types of devices. hwBufferModuleIndex - for the purpose of extension.In single CPU devices (NE16,eg.),hwBufferModuleIndex equals 0. hwBufferSize - the size in bytes of the buffer,such as 32 bytes,64 bytes, ...,etc.

children.name: hwBufferModuleIndex
children.description: The object is used only for the purpose of extension,In single CPU devices (NE16,eg.),hwBufferModuleIndex equals 0.

children.name: hwBufferSize
children.description: The object indicates the size of the buffers in bytes, such as 32 bytes, 64 bytes,...,etc.

children.name: hwBufferCurrentTotal
children.description: The object indicates the total number of the buffer currently.

children.name: hwBufferCurrentUsed
children.description: The object indicates the used number of the buffer currently.

children.name: hwFlashDevTable
children.description: This table contains falsh information.

children.name: hwFlashDevEntry
children.description: The Entries of hwFlashDevTable.

children.name: hwFlashDevIndex
children.description: Index of hwFlashDevTable.

children.name: hwFlashDevSize
children.description: Total size in Octets of Flash memory,

children.name: hwFlashDevFree
children.description: Unused Size in Octets of Flash memory.

children.name: hwFlashDevEraseTime
children.description: The last time when Flash was erased after powerup.

children.name: hwFlashDevEraseStatus
children.description: Status of current or last flash erasing.  Enumeration: 'bufferAllocationFailure': 6, 'flashErasing': 1, 'flashErasedSuccessful': 2, 'flashErasedFail': 3, 'flashOpenFailure': 5, 'flashReadOnly': 4, 'noEraseAfterPowerOn': 7.

children.name: hwFlashDevStatus
children.description: Status of the availability of flash.  Enumeration: 'available': 2, 'busy': 1.

children.name: hwAlarmTable
children.description: The table of Alarms which the device occurred.

children.name: hwAlarmEntry
children.description: The Entry of the Alarm Table.

children.name: hwAlarmSerialIndex
children.description: The Index of Alarms. Serial number.

children.name: hwAlarmType
children.description: The type of the Alarm.  Enumeration: 'restore': 2, 'alarm': 1, 'event': 3.

children.name: hwAlarmOcurTime
children.description: The time when this Alarm occurred.

children.name: trapObjectIdValue
children.description: The OID String of the trap.

children.name: hwFrameAdminResult
children.description: Frame administration result.  Enumeration: 'fail': 2, 'success': 1.

children.description: Slot administration result.  Enumeration: 'fail': 2, 'success': 1.

children.name: hwSubslotAdminResult
children.description: Subslot administration result.  Enumeration: 'fail': 2, 'success': 1.

children.name: hwPortAdminResult
children.description: Port administration result.  Enumeration: 'fail': 2, 'success': 1.

children.description: Slot administration result Trap report

children.description: Subslot administration result Trap report

children.description: Level of CLI user(1:common,2:operator,3:administrator).  Enumeration: 'operator': 2, 'administrator': 3, 'common': 1.

children.name: hwCliUserLogins
